===Etymology 1===
According to the ''Hànyǔ Tóngyuán Cí Dàdiǎn'' ({{lang|zh|漢語同源詞大典}}), this reading belongs to an Old Chinese word family centred on the concept of “smallness” or “finely divided things”. It is cognate with {{zh-l|鴲|small finch}} and {{zh-l|柴|twigs, fine wood}}. The semantic core—reducing an object into minute pieces—perfectly aligns with the classical definition of minced meat.

