====Definitions====
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# {{lb|zh|historical}} finely [[mince]]d [[fresh]], [[raw]] [[fish]] or [[meat]]
#* {{zh-x|《內則》謂 鮨 為 膾。|The ''Neize'' [chapter of the Book of Rites] refers to ''zhǐ'' as ''kuài'' (raw sliced meat).|ref=Eastern Han, Zheng Xuan's commentary on the ''{{w|Yili}}''}}
#* {{zh-x|聶 而 切 之 爲 膾。更 細 切 之，則 成 醬 爲 鮨 矣。鮨 者，膾 之 冣 細 者 也。|Slicing meat or fish into strips constitutes ''kuài''. Mincing it even more finely turns it into a paste, which is ''zhǐ''. Therefore, ''zhǐ'' is simply the finest, most minutely minced form of ''kuài''.|ref=Qing Dynasty, {{w|Duan Yucai}}, ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi Zhu}}''}}
# [[sushi]] {{gl|used as an orthographic borrowing from Japanese, distinguishing modern vinegared sushi from classical fermented ''[[narezushi]]'' ({{zh-l|鮓}})}}

===Etymology 2===
Derived from an Old Chinese root ''*g-rij'', sharing a phonetic relationship with the {{zh-l|*耆}} phonetic series. In historical texts, this character occasionally functioned as a phonetic variant for {{zh-l|鰭|tr=qí|fish fin}}.

