===Etymology 3===
A phonetic loan ({{zh-l|借字}}) for {{zh-l|鯢|tr=ní, yì|giant salamander}}. The ''{{w|Classic of Mountains and Seas}}'' describes the ''yì'' as an aquatic creature with the "voice of a baby" ({{lang|zh|其音如嬰兒}}), which is the classical hallmark of the Chinese giant salamander (colloquially known today as {{zh-l|娃娃魚|tr=wáwayú|baby fish}}). The character was borrowed purely for its Middle Chinese pronunciation (''ngiejH'') to represent the amphibian in regional mythography.

